The diode's nonlinear characteristic can be intentionally utilized to create piecewise-linear approximations of nonlinear functions. A common application is converting a triangular wave to a sine wave. Figure $1.18 a$ presents a simple instance of a piecewise-linear function generator. We observe the following:
